A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 3 of Article 16 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to student health, so as to prohibit public primary and secondary schools
3 from serving or selling, or allowing a third party to serve or sell, food or beverages that
4 contain synthetic dye; to provide for a definition; to provide for certification of compliance;
5 to provide legislative findings; to provide a short title; to provide for related matters; to
6 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Georgia Dye Free School Meals Act."
10 SECTION 2.
11 The General Assembly finds that:
12 (1) Scientific research has demonstrated that synthetic food dyes can contribute to
13 hyperactivity, inattention, restlessness, sleeplessness, irritability, aggression, and other
14 behavioral challenges in some children. These effects can impact a child's ability to
15 learn, focus, and participate in educational activities; and
